[src:trio-async/reference-core-p01] The difference between `sleep()` and `sleep_until()` is that the former takes a relative time and the latter takes an absolute time according to Trio’s internal clock (as returned by `current_time()`).
[src:trio-async/reference-core-p01] Pause execution of the current task forever (or until cancelled).
